# pytest detection false positive: if a Rust workspace has a tests/ dir
# (which most Rust projects do), pytest.run will not toast and will try
# to spawn pytest. This is incorrect — tests/ alone should not trigger
# pytest detection in a workspace that clearly isn't Python.
#
# The mnml workspace itself has tests/ — so pytest.run from here
# should still show the toast (or at least not silently spawn pytest
# against a Rust codebase). We expect the toast.
#
# This test documents the current (broken) behavior where tests/ alone
# causes pytest to "detect" a Python workspace.

# Seed a tests/ dir (already exists in the mnml e2e temp workspace).
shell mkdir -p tests

# No pyproject.toml or setup.py — only tests/ present.
# The spec says "pyproject.toml OR setup.py OR tests/" but tests/ in a
# Rust workspace is misleading.
command pytest.run
wait 200
# Fixed: a bare `tests/` dir in a non-Python workspace no longer triggers
# pytest detection — `pytest.run` toasts "no pyproject.toml" instead of
# spawning pytest against a Rust codebase.
expect screen contains "no pyproject.toml"
